<h1>How to convert square feet to acres<br></h1>
<!-- start: shared_blocks.119378400#below-h1 -->
<!-- end: shared_blocks.119378400#below-h1 -->
<p>In order to convert square feet to acres, first you need to know how man=
y square feet there are in an acre. By definition 1 acre is equal to 43560 =
square feet. </p><p>Study the example in the figure below carefully. It sho=
ws how to convert 130680 square feet to acres.</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Conte=
nt_1_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad  adthrive-content adthrive-content-1" sty=
le=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>
<!-- start: shared_blocks.119378391#below-paragraph-1 -->
<div class=3D"mobileOnly"></div>
<!-- end: shared_blocks.119378391#below-paragraph-1 -->
<div class=3D"CalloutBox" style=3D"box-sizing: border-box"><p>As you can se=
e from the example below, 1 acre is equal to 43560 square feet. This relati=
onship between square feet and acres can help you convert any area that is =
in square feet to acres.<br></p>
</div>
<div class=3D"ImageBlock ImageBlockCenter"><img src=3D"https://www.basic-ma=
thematics.com/images/square-feet-to-acres.png" width=3D"284" height=3D"313"=
 alt=3D"Square feet to acres" title=3D"Square feet to acres" data-pin-media=
=3D"https://www.basic-mathematics.com/images/square-feet-to-acres.png" styl=
e=3D"width: 284px; height: auto"></div>
<h2>More examples showing how to convert square feet to acres</h2>
<p><br><b>Example #1</b><br></p><p>Convert 87120 square feet to acres.</p><=
p>We can solve this problem by setting up a proportion the exact same way i=
t is demonstrated in the example in the figure above.<br></p><p>"If" <span =
style=3D"color: rgb(240, 0, 0);">43560</span> square feet is equal <span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(240, 0, 0);">1 acre</span>,</p><p>"then" <span style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(240, 0, 0);">87120</span> square feet is equal to <span style=3D"=
color: rgb(240, 0, 0);">x</span> acres.<br></p><p>Here is table that summar=
izes this problem.</p>
<table style=3D"color: #F00000" ;=3D"" border=3D"2" cellspadding=3D"10" wid=
th=3D"300">
<tbody><tr>
<td>43560</td>
<td>1 acre </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>87120</td>
<td>x</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<p>The proportion is 43560 / 87120 =3D 1 acre / x</p><p>After cross multipl=
ication, we get 43560 <span style=3D"text-align: left">=C3=97 x =3D 87120 <=
/span><span style=3D"text-align: left">=C3=97 1 acre</span></p><div id=3D"A=
dThrive_Content_2_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad  adthrive-content adthrive-c=
ontent-2" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div><p><span style=3D"text-align: =
left">43560x =3D 87120 acres</span></p><p><span style=3D"text-align: left">=
x =3D 87120 acres / 43560</span></p><p><span style=3D"text-align: left">x =
=3D 2 acres</span></p><p><span style=3D"text-align: left">87120 square feet=
 is equal to 2 acres.</span></p>
<div class=3D"CalloutBox" style=3D"box-sizing: border-box"><p>Notice how we=
 put the numbers in the table in the same order as they were in the "if-the=
n" sentence. It is very important to pull out the numbers in the same order=
!</p>
</div>
<p>Your "if-then" sentence could have been instead what you see below.</p><=
p>"If"&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(240, 0, 0);">1 acre</span>&nbsp;is eq=
ual <span style=3D"color: rgb(240, 0, 0);">&nbsp;43560 </span>square feet,<=
/p><p>"then" <span style=3D"color: rgb(240, 0, 0);">x acres</span>&nbsp;is =
equal to&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(240, 0, 0);">87120 </span>square fe=
et</p><p>Your table will then look a little bit different as you pull out t=
he numbers. However, you will still get the same answer when you set up the=
 proportion and solve it.</p>
<table style=3D"color: #F00000" ;=3D"" border=3D"2" cellspadding=3D"10" wid=
th=3D"300">
<tbody><tr>
<td> 1 acre</td>
<td>43560 </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>x</td>
<td>87120</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<p><b>Example #2<br></b></p><p>Convert 21780 square feet to acres.</p><p>Ag=
ain, this problem can be solved by setting up a proportion.<br></p><p>"If" =
43560&nbsp; square feet is equal 1 acre</p><p>"then" 21780 square feet is e=
qual to x acres<br></p><p>Here is table that summarizes this problem.</p>
<table border=3D"2" cellspadding=3D"10" width=3D"300">
<tbody><tr>
<td>43560</td>
<td>1 acre </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>21780</td>
<td>x</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_3_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad =
 adthrive-content adthrive-content-3" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>
<p>The proportion is 43560 / 21780 =3D 1 acre / x</p><p>After cross multipl=
ication, we get 43560 <span style=3D"text-align: left">=C3=97 x =3D 21780 <=
/span><span style=3D"text-align: left">=C3=97 1 acre</span></p><p><span sty=
le=3D"text-align: left">43560x =3D 21780 acres</span></p><p><span style=3D"=
text-align: left">x =3D 21780 acres / 43560</span></p><p><span style=3D"tex=
t-align: left">x =3D 0.5 acres</span></p><p><span style=3D"text-align: left=
">21780 square feet is equal to 0.5 acres.</span></p>
